Algorithm: Display Function
Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Check if the array size is equal to 0.
Condition: if (size == 0)
True:
Print "Array is empty".
Go to Step 8 (Stop).
False:
Continue to the next step.
Step 3: Print "Array elements:" to indicate that array elements will be displayed.
Step 4: Initialize a variable i = 0 (loop counter).
Step 5: Check the condition if (i < size).
True:
Print the element arr[i].
Increment i by 1 (i = i + 1).
Go back to Step 5 and repeat until i < size becomes False.
False:
Exit the loop.
Step 6: After printing all elements, end the loop.
Step 7: Stop the program.
